key
with
him?
But
that’s
not
all.
I
don’t
know,
Mr.
Utterson,
if
you
ever
met
this
Mr.
Hyde?”
“Yes,”
said
the
lawyer,
“I
once
spoke
with
him.”
“Then
you
must
know
as
well
as
the
rest
of
us
that
there
was
something
queer
about
that
gentleman--something
that
gave
a
man
a
turn--I
don’t
know
rightly
how
to
