like
ice.
O,
I
know
it’s
not
evidence,
Mr.
Utterson;
I’m
book-learned
enough
for
that;
but
a
man
has
his
feelings,
and
I
give
you
my
bible-word
it
was
Mr.
Hyde!”
“Ay,
ay,”
said
the
lawyer.
“My
fears
incline
to
the
same
point.
Evil,
I
fear,
founded--evil
was
sure
to
come--of
that
connection.
Ay
truly,
I
believe
you;
I
believe
poor
Harry
is
killed;
and
I
believe
his
murderer
(for
what
purpose,
God
alone
can
